Connecting the Unity API
Once the project is created and the proper references have been made, the first thing to do in order to leverage the API is to make a connection. At a minimum, there are two pieces of information required to make a connection to the Unity API, a URL (can be Application Server, Web Server, or Application Gateway Server), and an OnBase Datasource (that must be installed on the Server).

There are a number of ways to connect to OnBase in general, and the Unity API supports the majority of them. They will be covered in detail in the following pages.

