Unity Automation Toolkit
When implementing an Automation Interface, there is no need to perform any sort of connection since one has already been established in whatever client will be executing the script. Because of this, an already-connected Application will be provided in every interface method. It should be noted that this Application instance is only guaranteed to work within the context of the individual script and should not be passed to anything external to the script.

